any{{Citation needed|date=September 2013}}\n|-\n|Malaysia{{Citation needed|date=September 2013}}\n|-\n|New Zealand{{Citation needed|date=September 2013}}\n|-\n|Netherlands{{Citation needed|date=September 2013}}\n|-\n|United Kingdom{{Citation needed|date=September 2013}}\n|{{Start date|2013|08|26}}\n|-\n|Canada{{Citation needed|date=September 2013}}\n|rowspan=\"4\"|{{Start date|2013|08|27}}\n|-\n|Italy{{Citation needed|date=September 2013}}\n|-\n|South Korea{{Citation needed|date=September 2013}}\n|-\n|United States{{Citation needed|date=September 2013}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Avenged Sevenfold}}\n\n[[Category:2013 albums]]\n[[Category:Avenged Sevenfold albums]]\n[[Category:Warner Records albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Mike Elizondo]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded at Capitol Studios]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Hail to the King\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Avenged Sevenfold]]\n| cover      = A7XHailtotheKing.png\n| alt        =\n| released   = August 23, 2013\n| recorded   = 2013\n| venue      =\n| studio     = Can-Am Studios and [[Capitol Studios]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/avenged-sevenfold-confirmed-to-enter-studio-next-month |title=Avenged Sevenfold Confirmed to Enter Studio Next Month |work=[[Blabbermouth]] |date=December 21, 2012}}</ref>\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Heavy metal music|Heavy metal]]<ref name=\"LW - review\"/><ref name=\"about\"/>|[[hard rock]]<ref name=\"about\"/><ref name=\"killyourstereo\">{{cite web |url=http://www.killyourstereo.com/reviews/1348/avenged-sevenfold-hail-to-the-king/ |title=Avenged Sevenfold - Hail to the King |website=Killyourstereo.com |date=25 August 2013}}</ref>}}\n| length     = 53:20<br/>58:21 (with bonus)\n| label      = [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]]\n| producer   = [[Mike Elizondo]]\n| prev_title = [[Nightmare (Avenged Sevenfold album)|Nightmare]]\n| prev_year  = 2010\n| next_title = [[The Stage (album)|The Stage]]\n| next_year  = 2016\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Hail to the King\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Hail to the King (song)|Hail to the King]]\n | single1date = July 15, 2013\n | single2     = [[Shepherd of Fire]]\n | single2date = November 7, 2013\n | single3     = [[This Means War (Avenged Sevenfold song)|This Means War]]\n | single3date = July 4, 2014\n}}\n{{Extra album cover\n | header  = Vinyl Cover\n | type    = studio\n | cover   = HailToTheKingVinyl.jpeg\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption =\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Hail to the King''''' is the sixth [[studio album]] by American [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] band [[Avenged Sevenfold]]. It was released on August 23, 2013 in [[New Zealand]] and [[Australia]], and was released on [[iTunes]] on August 27, 2013 and in North America on the same day. The album was produced by [[Mike Elizondo]]. ''Hail to the King'' is the only Avenged Sevenfold album to feature drummer Arin Ilejay, prior to his departure in July 2015. It is also the first Avenged Sevenfold album without musical contributions from Ilejay's late predecessor, [[The Rev|Jimmy \"The Rev\" Sullivan]]; the bonus track, \"St. James\", was written in his memory.\n\nThe album was a commercial and critical success, reaching number 1 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]. This marks Avenged Sevenfold's second album to top the ''Billboard'' chart (the first being ''[[Nightmare (Avenged Sevenfold album)|Nightmare]]''), as well as their first to reach number 1 in the UK, topping the [[UK Albums Chart]]. It also topped the Canadian, Brazilian, Finnish and Irish album charts. Also, the album spawned two number 1 singles on Billboard's Mainstream Rock, Hail to the King, and Shepherd of Fire. The former spent 11 weeks on the top of the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.billboard.com/artist/280315/avenged-sevenfold/chart?f=376|title = Avenged Sevenfold|publisher = Nielsen Inc.|accessdate = 4 October 2014|website = billboard.com}}</ref> On July 16, 2014 the album was certified [[Gold record|Gold]] by the [[RIAA]] for sales of over 500,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|title = Avenged Sevenfold's 'Hail To The King' Certified Gold In U.S.|url = http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/avenged-sevenfolds-hail-to-the-king-certified-gold-in-u-s/|website = blabbermouth.net|accessdate = August 24, 2014|date = July 26, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nOn November 15, 2012, vocalist [[M. Shadows]] said that the band has been working on a new album since the recording of \"[[Carry On (Avenged Sevenfold song)|Carry On]]\" in August 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=182300|title = Avenged Sevenfold Singer Says New Album Is 'Coming Along Nicely'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date = November 15, 2012|accessdate = 2012-11-17}}</ref> In December, the band said that it plans to begin recording material for their next album in January 2013, with release planned for later in the year.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=183921|title = Avenged Sevenfold Confirmed To Enter Studio Next Month|website=Blabbermouth.net|date = December 21, 2012|accessdate = }}</ref> In January 2013 the band started recording their new album. The band started streaming snippets of their new album in May 2013 on their new radio app.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Avenged Sevenfold Launch New Website, Tease Forthcoming Album|url = http://kroq.cbslocal.com/2013/05/09/avenged-sevenfold-launch-new-website-tease-forthcoming-album/|accessdate = 2015-06-03|website = kroq.com|date = May 9, 2013|publisher = CBS Local Media}}</ref> It was on the app that Arin Ilejay was confirmed as an official band member and replacement of deceased drummer and founding member [[The Rev]]. In an interview with ''[[Metal Hammer]]'' about the new album, M. Shadows said that the album would sound more [[blues rock]]-influenced and more like classic rock and classic metal in the vein of [[Black Sabbath]] and [[Led Zeppelin]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.avengedsevenfold.com/content/metal-hammer-m-shadows-wants-new-avenged-sevenfold-album-be-metalrock-classic |title=M Shadows Wants The New Avenged Sevenfold Album To Be A Metal/Rock Classic |website=Metal Hammer |date=2013-02-13 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130621124918/http://www.avengedsevenfold.com/content/metal-hammer-m-shadows-wants-new-avenged-sevenfold-album-be-metalrock-classic |archive-date=2013-06-21 |df= }} The new album has a lot more of a Sabbath and Zeppelin feel to it, \u201d he states. \u201cThere\u2019s definitely more Sabbath in what we\u2019re writing, and we\u2019re proud of \u2018Carry On,\u2019 but this album is going to be on a whole new level. We\u2019re shooting for late January, early February [to enter the studio] and to have the album out in the summer. I\u2019m pretty sure that we\u2019re looking to go overseas first, so you guys will be seeing it before everyone else... We\u2019re going back to Sabbath stuff. We\u2019re looking at blues chords they\u2019re playing most of their stuff in. We\u2019re listening to Zeppelin. We\u2019re going backwards with what we want this record to feel like. I wanna write a classic metal record, a classic rock record in 2013.</ref>\n\nThe band released four teasers on YouTube showing the band going through the recording process as well as providing snippets of songs off the album. On June 26, 2013, the band revealed the title, cover art and release date of album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.revolvermag.com/news/avenged-sevenfold-reveal-cover-art-title-and-release-date-of-new-album.html|website=Revolvermag|title=Avenged Sevenfold Reveal Cover Art, Title, and Release Date of New Album|accessdate=June 26, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=191807|website=Blabbermouth.net|title=AVENGED SEVENFOLD: New Album Title, Cover Artwork, Release Date Revealed|accessdate=June 26, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aRPiPb_UcdI&feature=player_embedded|title=Avenged Sevenfold - Hail to the King [Preview]|work=YouTube|accessdate=4 October 2014}}</ref> In July, the band revealed the complete track list of the album.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kerrang.com/blog/2013/07/avenged_sevenfold_unveil_track.html# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2013-08-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130827171220/http://www.kerrang.com/blog/2013/07/avenged_sevenfold_unveil_track.html# |archive-date=2013-08-27 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\nOn August 8, 2013, \"Shepherd of Fire\" was revealed to be the theme song of the ''[[Call of Duty: Black Ops II]]'' Zombies map \"Origins\", included in its final [[downloadable content]] pack titled ''Apocalypse''.<ref>{{cite web|title=AVENGED SEVENFOLD: Trailer For 'Hail To The King' Animated Series|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/avenged-sevenfold-trailer-for-hail-to-the-king-animated-series/|website=Blabbermouth}}</ref>\n\n==Musical style==\n[[Synyster Gates]] stated of the album: \"I think our songwriting has improved by leaps and bounds. Sonically, this record is our biggest record by fucking far. When you turn this fucking thing on, it blasts your fucking head off.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.revolvermag.com/news/lyrics-avenged-sevenfol.html|title=Avenged Sevenfold\u2019s Synyster Gates on the New Album and His Guitar Center and Schecter Guitar Research Master Class |website=Revolvermag |accessdate=4 October 2014}}</ref> [[M. Shadows]] stated about the album's music: \"On this record, we want a very bare bones, [[riff]]-oriented approach. Because it's really easy for us to say 'That melody would sound great here, throw this background vocal here, here's this harmony.' We had to restrain ourselves from doing that just to keep it more badass and just more straightforward  [[rock music|rock]].\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Avenged Sevenfold Singer Talks New Record: 'It's More Bada-s, Straightforward Rock'|url=http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/upcoming_releases/avenged_sevenfold_singer_talks_new_record_its_more_bada-s_straightforward_rock.html|website=Ultimate-Guitar}}</ref>\n\n[[Zacky Vengeance]] stated: \"We styled everything back and went to the core of [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] instead of trying to overcomplicate it. We wrote and wrote, and felt we really achieved what we were going for ... we're really proud of what we've come up with.\" <ref>{{cite web|title=Avenged Sevenfold on New Album: 'We Went to the Core of Heavy Metal'|url=http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/upcoming_releases/avenged_sevenfold_on_new_album_we_went_to_the_core_of_heavy_metal.html|website=Ultimate Guitar}}</ref> [[Johnny Christ]] stated about the album's musical style in an interview with [[bravewords]]: \"It's definitely us. It's just the next progression. It's probably the heaviest record that we've put out - in its own right. It's been a great response for the single ([[Hail to the King (song)|Hail to the King]]) so far, which I feel is a good way to see what the rest of the record is going to sound like. There will be some surprises in there for fans, but overall, I'm just excited.\" He also said the album is more  [[groove metal]]-oriented.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bravewords.com/news/207995|title=AVENGED SEVENFOLD Bassist Talks New Album, Upcoming Heavy MTL Festival Appearance - \"It's A Little Bit More Of A Throwback To Some Our Heroes In Music - It's More Groove Metal-oriented, A Little Bit More Mature\"|work=bravewords.com|accessdate=4 October 2014}}</ref> The album also shows a thrash metal sound, with fast to mid-paced tempos, heavily distorted guitars and war, religious intolerance or corruption themed lyrics.\n\n==Release and promotion==\nOn July 15, 2013 the album was made available for pre-order and the title track, \"[[Hail to the King (song)|Hail to the King]]\", was released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/avenged-sevenfold-deftones-ghost-b-c-fall-2013-u-s-tour/|work=[[Loudwire]]|title=Avenged Sevenfold, Deftones and Ghost B.C. to Embark on Fall 2013 U.S. Tour |accessdate=July 16, 2013|date=July 15, 2013|first=Chad|last=Bowar}}</ref>\n\nThe same day, the band revealed a Limited Edition of ''Hail to the King'' for [[pre-order]] available on their website, much as they did with their previous album, ''[[Nightmare (Avenged Sevenfold album)|Nightmare]]''. The limited edition set included:\n\n* Limited Edition \u201cTreasure Box\u201d: Antique gold colored embossed foil paper wrapped box featuring exclusive ''Hail To The King'' artwork\n* Deluxe ''Hail To The King'' album on CD: Housed in a digi-pak with a card including a download to an extra bonus track\n* Exclusive Canvas Print: 11.75\u2033 \u00d7 11.75\u2033 Canvas print of the Album Cover artwork, printed and rolled up to fit inside the treasure box\n* Photo Book: 11.5\u2033 \u00d7 7.125\u2033 20-page + cover perfect-bound soft-cover book featuring a sampling of photos of the band throughout the years\n* Death Bat Challenge Coin: 2\u2033 silver colored metal coin with a design stamped on front & back\n* Death Bat Skeleton Key: 4.5\u2033 silver colored metal skeleton key\n* Digital Content: Instant download ''Hail To The King'' Single. Download of ''Hail To The King'' album on street date\n* Pre-Sale access to the upcoming Avenged Sevenfold US Tour<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avengedsevenfold.com/hailtotheking/|title=Avenged Sevenfold Hail to the King|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902022144/http://www.avengedsevenfold.com/hailtotheking/|archive-date=2013-09-02|df=}}</ref>\n\nOn August 19, 2013, the album was made available for streaming on iTunes.<ref>{{cite web|title=AVENGED SEVENFOLD: Entire 'Hail To The King' Album Available For Streaming|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/avenged-sevenfold-entire-hail-to-the-king-album-avaiable-for-streaming/|website=Blabbermouth}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| ADM = 6.7/10<ref name=\"ADM\">{{cite web |title=Avenged Sevenfold Hail to the King |url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/5780/Avenged-Sevenfold-Hail-to-the-King.aspx |website=[[AnyDecentMusic?]] |accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref>\n| MC = 70/100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/hail-to-the-king/avenged-sevenfold|title=Hail to the King Reviews|website=Metacritic.com|accessdate=2013-08-30}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[About.com]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"about\">{{cite web |url=http://heavymetal.about.com/od/avengedsevenfold/fr/Avenged-Sevenfold-Hail-To-The-King-Review.htm |title=Avenged Sevenfold \u2013 Hail to the King Review |website=[[About.com]] |access-date=31 August 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130907182139/http://heavymetal.about.com/od/avengedsevenfold/fr/Avenged-Sevenfold-Hail-To-The-King-Review.htm# |archive-date=2013-09-07 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n| rev2 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev2score = {{Rating|2.5|5}}<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/hail-to-the-king-mw0002561282|title=Hail to the King \u2013 Avenged Sevenfold|work=[[AllMusic]]|first=Jason|last=Lymangrover|date=August 29, 2013|accessdate=August 29, 2013}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]''\n| rev3score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"AP - review\">{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/reviews/entry/avenged_sevenfold_hail_to_the_king|title=Avenged Sevenfold \u2013 Hail to the King|work=[[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]|first=Dan|last=Slessor|date=August 27, 2013|accessdate=August 27, 2013}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n| rev4score = {{rating|4|10}}<ref name=\"exclaim - review\">{{cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/Reviews/Metal/avenged_sevenfold-hail_to_king|title=Avenged Sevenfold \u2013 Hail to the King|work=[[Exclaim!]]|first=Bradley|last=Zorgdrager|date=August 23, 2013|accessdate=August 28, 2013}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev5score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"guardian - review\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2013/aug/22/avenged-sevenfold-hail-king-review|title=Avenged Sevenfold: Hail to the King \u2013 review|work=[[The Guardian]]|publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]]|first=Dom|last=Lawson|date=August 22, 2013|accessdate=August 27, 2013}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[Kerrang]]''\n| rev6score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/hail-to-the-king/avenged-sevenfold/critic-reviews|title=Critic Reviews for Hail to the King - Metacritic|work=Metacritic}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[Loudwire]]''\n| rev7score = {{rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=\"LW - review\">{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/avenged-sevenfold-hail-to-the-king-album-review|title=Avenged Sevenfold, 'Hail to the King' \u2013 Album Review|work=[[Loudwire]]|first=Chris|last=Epting|date=August 28, 2013|accessdate=August 28, 2013}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[The New Zealand Herald]]''\n| rev8score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"NZ Herald - review\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=11115746|title=Album review: Avenged Sevenfold, Hail to the King|work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|first=Scott|last=Kara|date=August 28, 2013|accessdate=August 28, 2013}}</ref>\n| rev9 = ''[[The Oakland Press]]''\n| rev9score = {{Rating|3|4}}<ref name=oaklandpress>{{cite web|last=Graff |first=Gary |authorlink=Gary Graff |url=http://www.theoaklandpress.com/articles/2013/08/26/entertainment/doc5217b0cead3b4760069156.txt |title=Listening Room: \"Hall of Fame\" puts Big Sean on the path to immortality |work=[[The Oakland Press]] |date=August 26, 2013 |accessdate=August 28, 2013}}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev10score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"RS - review\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/hail-to-the-king-20130827|title=Avenged Sevenfold, 'Hail to the King'|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|first=Jon|last=Dolan|date=August 27, 2013|accessdate=August 27, 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Hail to the King'' received positive reviews upon release. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a [[Standard score|normalized]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream music critics, the album received an [[Weighted arithmetic mean|average]] score of 70, based on 9 reviews, which indicates \"generally favorable\" reviews. At [[AnyDecentMusic?]], that collates critical reviews from more than 50 media sources, the album scored 6.7 points out of 10, based on eight reviews.<ref name=\"ADM\" />\n\nIn a summary of his review, Chris Epting of ''[[Loudwire]]'' called the album \"a modern metal classic that reflects the past while very much embracing the present\".<ref name=\"LW - review\"/> [[Artistdirect]]'s Rick Florino stated, \"Hail to the King doesn't just raise the bar for the band, but it raises the bar for everyone else to follow and compete with.\" In a very positive review, Dom Lawson of ''[[The Guardian]]'' judged, \"Stripped down to a core of thudding Sabbath-like grooves and brash, spiky vocal refrains, Avenged now sound every bit as vital and imperious as the bands they aspire to emulate.\"<ref name=\"guardian - review\"/> \"''Hail to the King'' represents a clean sweep, a divergence into classic metal and their best chance of hitting the heights they've always longed for\", according to ''[[Q (magazine)|Q]]''. \"The next giant crossover metal band has arrived\", reviewer Tom Bryant concluded, giving the album a 4 stars out of 5 rating.<ref name=\"q\">Bryant, Tom. [[Q (magazine)|Q]], November 2013. Record reviews. New releases. Avenged Sevenfold \u2013 hail to the King. P. 101</ref>\n\nNot all critics were as enthusiastic. In a mixed review, Jason Lymangrover of [[AllMusic]] remarked: \"Unfortunately, once they tried to take inspiration from other bands, they mimicked them so well that they lost their sense of identity in the process\". He also accused \"This Means War\" of ripping off [[Metallica]]'s song \"[[Sad but True]]\".<ref name=\"allmusic\"/> In a more negative review, Bradley Zorgdrager of ''[[Exclaim!]]'' said: \"After it concludes, ''Hail to the King'' makes it challenging for listeners to recall any specific moment, which defeats the purpose of a pop (metal) album\". The album also has been compared to bands like [[Iron Maiden]], [[Metallica]], and [[Pantera]].<ref name=\"allmusic\"/><ref name=\"AEaston\">{{cite web |url=http://hangout.altsounds.com/reviews/161193-review-avenged-sevenfold-hail-king-album.html |title=Review: Avenged Sevenfold \u2013 Hail to the King [Album] |website=altsounds.com |publisher=AEaston |date=August 21, 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130824151345/http://hangout.altsounds.com/reviews/161193-review-avenged-sevenfold-hail-king-album.html |archive-date=August 24, 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\nIn a blog post, [[Machine Head (band)|Machine Head]] frontman [[Robb Flynn]] was also very critical of the album, denouncing it as a mere \"cover album\" and making several jokes about the similarities a selection of songs share with those by [[Metallica]], [[Megadeth]], and [[Guns N' Roses]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metalhammer.co.uk/news/machine-heads-robb-flynn-on-hail-to-the-king-who-knew-that-re-recording-metallica-could-be-such-a-hit|title=Machine Head\u2019s Robb Flynn On \u2018Hail To The King\u2019: Who Knew That Rerecording Metallica Could Be Such A Hit?!|website=Metal Hammer}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/machine-head-robb-flynn-avenged-sevenfold-hail-to-the-king-covers-album/|title=Machine Head's Robb Flynn Calls Avenged Sevenfold's 'Hail to the King' a 'Covers Album'|work=Loudwire|accessdate=4 October 2014}}</ref> M. Shadows responded to the criticism saying that he \"read it as a joke\", but noted that \"if it is a joke, it was kind of overboard\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/avenged-sevenfold-singer-responds-to-machine-head-frontmans-covers-album-critique|title=AVENGED SEVENFOLD Singer Responds To MACHINE HEAD Frontman's 'Covers Album' Critique|website=Blabbermouth}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Region\n!Year\n!Publication\n!Accolade\n!Rank\n|-\n|United States\n|2015\n|[[Loudwire]]\n|10 Best Rock Albums of 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/best-metal-riffs-2000s/ |title= 10 Best Rock Albums of 2013 |website=Loudwire |date= |accessdate=}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|5\n|}\n\n'''Loudwire Music Awards'''\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n| 2013 || Hail to the King || Rock Album of the Year || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2013 || Hail to the King || Best Rock Song || {{won}}\n{{end}}\n\n'''Revolver Golden Gods Awards'''\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n| 2014 || Hail to the King || Album of the Year || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2014 || Hail to the King || Song of the Year || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2014 || M. Shadows || Best Vocalist || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2014 || Synyster Gates & Zacky Vengeance || Best Guitarists || {{won}}\n|-\n| 2014 || Arin Ilejay || Best Drummer || {{won}}\n|-\n| 2014 || Johnny Christ || Best Bassist || {{nom}}\n{{end}}\n\n==Commercial performance==\n''Hail to the King'' debuted at number one on the UK Albums Chart on September 1, 2013.{{r|UK chart}} It also debuted at number two on the [[The Official Finnish Charts|Official Finnish Albums Chart]]{{r|FIN chart}} and at number five in Germany.{{citation needed|date=January 2015}}\n\nThe album sold 159,000 copies in the United States in its first week of release to debut at number one on the ''Billboard'' 200 chart.<ref>{{cite web|title=AVENGED SEVENFOLD's 'Hail To The King' Tops U.S. Chart|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/avenged-sevenfolds-hail-to-the-king-tops-u-s-chart/|website=Blabbermouth}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\nAll songs written and composed by M. Shadows, Zacky Vengeance, Synyster Gates, and Johnny Christ.\n{{tracklist\n| title1 = [[Shepherd of Fire]]\n| length1 = 5:25\n| title2 = [[Hail to the King (song)|Hail to the King]]\n| length2 = 5:06\n| title3 = Doing Time\n| length3 = 3:27\n| title4 = [[This Means War (Avenged Sevenfold song)|This Means War]]\n| length4 = 6:09\n| title5 = Requiem\n| length5 = 4:23\n| title6 = Crimson Day\n| length6 = 5:02\n| title7 = Heretic\n| length7 = 5:00\n| title8 = Coming Home\n| length8 = 6:26\n| title9 = Planets\n| length9 = 6:01\n| title10 = Acid Rain\n| length10 = 6:40\n|total_length = 53:34\n}}\n\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Deluxe version bonus tracks<ref name=itunes>{{cite web|title=Hail to the King (Deluxe Version)|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/hail-to-king-deluxe-version/id672046420|publisher=iTunes|accessdate=15 July 2013}}</ref> \n| collapsed = yes\n| title11 = Hail to the King\n| note11 = music video\n| length11 = 5:13\n| title12 = St. James\n| note12 = lyrics: Synyster Gates\n| length12 = 5:01\n|total_length = 63:34\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n'''Avenged Sevenfold'''\n* [[M. Shadows]] \u2013 lead vocals\n* [[Zacky Vengeance]] \u2013 rhythm guitar, backing vocals\n* [[Synyster Gates]] \u2013 lead guitar, backing vocals, additional vocals on \"Planets\", co-lead vocals on \"Doing Time\"\n* [[Johnny Christ]] \u2013 bass guitar, backing vocals\n* Arin Ilejay \u2013 drums, percussion\n\n'''Session musicians'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/hail-to-the-king-mw0002561282/credits|title=Hail to the King - Avenged Sevenfold \u2013 Credits \u2013 AllMusic|work=AllMusic|accessdate=4 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n* Storm Lee Gardner \u2013 Vocals on \"Requiem\"\n* Ran Jackson \u2013 Vocals on \"Requiem\"\n* Jessi Collins \u2013 Vocals on \"Requiem\"\n* Sharlotte Gibson \u2013 Vocals on \"Requiem\"\n* Rick D. Waserman \u2013 Voice-over on \"Requiem\"\n* Brent Arrowood \u2013 Sound effects on \"Shepherd of Fire\"  \n* [[Brian Haner|Brian Haner Sr]] \u2013 Outro guitar solo on \"Coming Home\"\n* [[David Campbell (composer)|David Campbell]] \u2013 Orchestra arranger & conductor\n* Suzie Katayama - [[cello]] on \"Shepherd of Fire\", \"Requiem\", \"Crimson Day\", \"Planets\" and \"Acid Rain\"\n* Dane Little, John E. Acosta \u2013 cello on \"Requiem\", \"Crimson Day\" and \"Acid Rain\"\n* Charlie Bisharat, John Wittenberg, Josefina Vergara, Michelle Richards, Natalie Leggett, Sara Parkins, Songa Lee, Tereza Stanislav \u2013 [[violin]] on \"Requiem\", \"Crimson Day\" and \"Acid Rain\"\n* Ed Meares - [[upright bass]] on \"Shepherd of Fire\", \"Requiem\" and \"Planets\"\n* [[John Fumo]], Rick Baptist \u2013 [[trumpet]] on \"Shepherd of Fire\", \"Requiem\" and \"Planets\"\n* Jeff Babko \u2013 [[piano]] on \"Acid Rain\"\n* Alan Kaplan \u2013 [[trombone]] on \"Shepherd of Fire\", \"Requiem\" and \"Planets\"\n* Steven Holtman, Andrew Martin, Jaime Ochoa - [[bass trombone]] on \"Shepherd of Fire\", \"Requiem\" and \"Planets\"\n* Douglas Tornquist \u2013 [[tuba]] on \"Shepherd of Fire\", \"Requiem\" and \"Planets\"\n* Joe Meyer, John Reynolds \u2013 [[French horn|horn]] on \"Shepherd of Fire\", \"Requiem\" and \"Planets\"\n\n'''Production'''\n* [[Mike Elizondo]] \u2013 [[Record producer|production]], [[keyboard instrument|keyboards]] on \"Crimson Day\", \"Heretic\" and \"Coming Home\", sound effects on \"Shepherd of Fire\" and \"Acid Rain\"\n* Allen Wolfe \u2013 [[A&R]]\n* Joanna Terrasi \u2013 A&R\n* Brent Arrowood \u2013 assistant engineer\n* Chris Sporleder \u2013 assistant engineer\n* D.A. Frizell \u2013 illustrations, treatment\n* Adam Hawkins \u2013 engineer\n* Paul Suarez \u2013 pro-tools\n* Cam Rackman \u2013 [[paintings]], [[portraits]]\n* [[Andy Wallace (producer)|Andy Wallace]] \u2013 [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixer]]\n* [[Bob Ludwig]] \u2013 [[mastering engineer]]\n\n==Charts and certifications==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n!Chart (2013)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{Albumchart|Australia|2|artist=Avenged Sevenfold|album=Hail To The King|refname=AUS chart|accessdate=2013-09-02}}\n|-\n{{Albumchart|Austria|3|artist=Avenged Sevenfold|album=Hail To The King|refname=AU chart|accessdate=2013-09-02}}\n|-\n{{Albumchart|Flanders|30|artist=Avenged Seve