ec precipitation days = 7.1\n|year precipitation days = \n|source = Servizio Meteorologico<ref name=Servizio>{{cite web\n|url=http://clima.meteoam.it/viewClino.php?type=File&station=490&name_station=Isole\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170226215817/http://clima.meteoam.it/viewClino.php?type=File&station=490&name_station=Isole\n|archivedate=26 February 2017\n|publisher =Servizio Meteorologico\n|title=Stazione 490 Lampedusa\n|accessdate=13 October 2012}}</ref>\n|source 2 =<ref name=extremes>{{cite web\n|url = http://climaintoscana.altervista.org/italia/stazioni-wmo/lampedusa/\n|title = Lampedusa \n|publisher = Temperature estreme in Toscana\n|language = Italian\n|accessdate = 13 May 2017}}</ref>{{unreliable source|date=December 2017|reason=a community site hosted in altervista.org}}\n|date=January 2011\n}}\n\n== In popular culture ==\n* Lampedusa was the filming location for the music video of [[Mango (singer)|Mango]]'s single \"Mediterraneo\", from the album ''[[Come l'acqua]]'' (1992).<ref>{{cite web|title=\"Scusate\". Poi Mango muore |author=|publisher=noinotizie.it|url=http://www.noinotizie.it/08-12-2014/e-morto-mango/|accessdate=3 February 2015|language=it}}</ref>\n* The [[Film|movie]] ''[[Respiro]]'' (2002), written and directed by [[Emanuele Crialese]] and starring [[Valeria Golino]], was filmed entirely on Lampedusa.\n* The book ''The Pharaoh's Secret'' (2015) by popular fiction author [[Clive Cussler]] features Lampedusa as the scene of a mysterious deathly mist.\n*''[[Think of Lampedusa]]'' collection of poems by the 2014 [[Tchicaya U Tam'si Prize for African Poetry |Tchicaya U Tam'si Prize]] Josu\u00e9 Gu\u00e9bo, refers to the [[2013 Lampedusa migrant shipwreck|2013 shipwreck]] near Lampedusa.\n* The 2015 Austrian documentary ''[[Lampedusa im Winter]]'', directed by [[Jakob Brossmann]] was filmed on the island.\n* The 2016 book ''Tears of Salt: A Doctor's Story by'' [[Pietro Bartolo]] and Lidia Tilitta recounts life on the island and the migrant crisis through the lens of a local doctor.\n* The 2017 Oscar-nominated Italian documentary, ''[[Fire at Sea]]'', was filmed entirely on the island between 2014 and 2015.\n* ''Lampedusa'' is the title of the 2019 novelised biography of [[Giuseppe Tomasi di Lampedusa]] by Canadian novelist Steven Price.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of islands of Italy]]\n* [[Linosa]]\n* [[Pantelleria]]\n* [[Pelagie Islands]]\n* [[LORAN-C transmitter Lampedusa]]\n* [[Lampedusa Airport]]\n* [[Quadro Group]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/3712052.stm BBC News \u2013 Italy Deports Island Immigrants] \u2013 Covers the changing face of immigration in 2004\n* [https://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-35540017 \"Why tourists are shunning a beautiful Italian island\"] - [[BBC News]], 13 February 2015\n\n{{Portalbar|Geography|Islands|Italy}}\n{{Pelagian Islands}}\n\n{{Outlying territories of European countries}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Lampedusa e Linosa]]\n[[Category:Pelagie Islands]]\n[[Category:Coastal towns in Sicily]]\n[[Category:Frazioni of the Province of Agrigento]]\n[[Category:Islands of Africa]]\n", "name_user": "SelfieCity", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eClimate", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lampedusa"}
{"title_page": "Radio Arvyla", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Radio Arvyla\n| image                    = Radio arvyla.jpg\n| genre                    = Satirical Talk-Show\n| creator                  = Antonis Kanakis\n| director                 = Antonis Kanakis\n| presenter                = Antonis Kanakis<br> Giannis Servetas<br> Stathis Panagiotopoulos<br> Christos Kiousis<br>\n| composer                 = \n| opentheme                = \"[[Sugar Baby Love]]\"<br>by [[The Rubettes]] <ref>http://www.musicheaven.gr/html/modules.php?name=Splatt_Forums&file=viewtopic&topic=15248</ref>\n| country                  = [[Greece]]\n| language                 = [[Greek language|Greek]]\n| num_seasons              = 11\n| runtime                  = 90 minutes\n| network                  = [[ANT1]] (2008-2018)<br> [[Skai TV]] (2019)<br>[[YouTube]](2020-)\n| picture_format           = [[576i]] [[SDTV]]<br>[[1080i]] [[HDTV]]\n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = 14 April 2008\n| preceded_by              = [[A.M.A.N. (TV series)|A.M.A.N.]]\n| related                  = \n| website                  = http://www.antenna.gr/radioarvyla\n}}\n'''''Radio Arvyla''''' ({{lang-el|\u03a1\u03ac\u03b4\u03b9\u03bf \u0391\u03c1\u03b2\u03cd\u03bb\u03b1}}) is a Greek live panel show, filmed in [[Thessaloniki]] and airing on [[ANT1]].<ref>http://www.antenna.gr/minisites/radio-arvila/home</ref> It first aired on April 2008. It is hosted by [[Antonis Kanakis]], Giannis Servetas, Stathis Panagiotopoulos and Christos Kiousis. This live show focuses primarily on the sociopolitical issues affecting Greece, especially with regards to the long-term fiscal crisis via the use of political commentary and various forms of makeshift parodies, montage and satire. \nAs of 2016-17 season, it airs every other Monday, from 23.15 to 00.30, although it used to air from 18.00 to 19.00 during the 2007-2008 and 2008-2009 seasons. The first episode of season 4 aired on 11 October 2010.<ref>http://www.e-daily.gr/viral/74070/radio-arvyla-kathe-pote-tha-provalletai-h-ekpomph-video</ref><ref>http://www.gossip-tv.gr/media-tv/story/468944/h-epistrofi-ton-radio-arvyla-kai-i-anakoinosi-toy-antoni-kanaki</ref> All episodes from Season 3 and on are available online on the official website of [[ANT1]].<ref>http://www.antenna.gr/minisites/radio-arvila/episodes</ref><ref>http://www.newsit.gr/melas-blogposts/telos-oi-radio-arvyla/2207539/</ref><ref>http://www.iefimerida.gr/news/360613/anatropi-me-radio-arvyla-ti-tha-ginei-telika-me-tin-dimofili-ekpompi-toy-ant1</ref><ref>http://www.protothema.gr/life-style/article/711259/anatropi-me-to-radio-arvula-ti-pragmatika-sumvainei-me-tin-ekpobi-tou-adoni-kanaki/</ref>.\n\n==Format==\n\nThe show begins with the segment \"The bad joke of the day,\" where Stathis Panagiotopoulos tells a joke that is considered \"cold\". Afterwards, the \"Top of the week\" (\"Top \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03ba\u03b1\u03b9\u03c1\u03cc\u03c4\u03b7\u03c4\u03b1\u03c2\") segment begins, where videos from various events that occurred are shown, categorized into (usually 25) numbers, for which there are satirical videos (comic skits, parodies etc.) that make fun of the original videos that were presented earlier. At the end of every episode, there is live music from (usually) new and up-and-coming bands. Internationally famous acts have also appeared, like The Zombies and Tim Booth.\n\nUntil the 6th season, Evgenia Samara or Christina Moustaka would be presenting funny videos found online or created by fans of the show, after the end of \"Top of the week\".\n\nStarting with the 7th season, in which only one episode was airing per week, sketches have been incorporated into the format of the show. Besides the hosts, Kostas, the floor manager, and Stathis, a cameraman, make usual appearances in those sketches. Kostas (referred to as Kostakis) and Stathis (referred to as Pasoktsis) have been a part of some of the show's inside jokes for a while.\n\nAn invaluable and much loved member of the group was Sardela, Stathis' dog. She would come along to every taping and could be seen walking around the set. She passed away after the end of season 8. The hosts paid tribute to her on the first episode of season 9.\n\n==Episodes==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; width: 50%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"padding:0 8px; width:5%;\" rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"| Season\n! style=\"padding:0 8px; width:20%;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Episodes\n! style=\"padding:0 80px; width:75%;\" colspan=\"2\"| Originally aired\n|-\n! First aired\n! Last aired\n|-\n| style=\"background:#0048BA; color:#100; text-align:center;\"|\n| '''1'''\n| 54\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 14 April 2008\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 27 June 2008\n|-\n| style=\"background:#6D9A79; color:#100; text-align:center;\" |\n|  '''2'''\n| 45\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 6 October 2008\n| 10 June 2009\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FFCC00; color:#100; text-align:center;\" |\n|  '''3'''\n| 141\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 5 October 2009\n| 3 June 2010\n|-\n| style=\"background:#8BBE1B; color:#100; text-align:center;\" |\n|  '''4'''\n| 99\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 11 October 2010\n| 8 June 2011\n|-\n| style=\"background:#9D296E; color:#100; text-align:center;\" |\n|  '''5'''\n| 90\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 24 October 2011\n| 30 May 2012\n|-\n| style=\"background:#E75480; color:#100; text-align:center;\" |\n|  '''6'''\n| 66\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 29 October 2012\n| 4 June 2013\n|-\n| style=\"background:#720B98; color:#100; text-align:center;\" |\n|  '''7'''\n| 26\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 11 November 2013\n| 2 June 2014\n|-\n| style=\"background:#2F847C; color:#100; text-align:center;\"|\n| '''8'''\n| 24\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 17 November 2014\n| 8 June 2015\n|-\n| style=\"background:#B31B1B; color:#100; text-align:center;\"|\n| '''9'''\n| 24\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 23 November 2015\n| 6 June 2016\n|-\n| style=\"background:#24A0ED; color:#100; text-align:center;\"|\n| '''10'''\n| 15\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 21 November 2016\n| 5 June 2017\n|-\n| style=\"background:#36454F; color:#100; text-align:center;\"|\n| '''11'''\n| 22(+1)\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 27 November 2017\n| 4 June 2018\n|-\n| style=\"background:#36D6E5; color:#100; text-align:center;\"|\n| '''12'''\n| 16\n| style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" | 4 February 2019<ref>http://www.skai.gr/news/media/article/395147/to-proto-treiler-tou-radio-arvula-ston-skai-video/</ref>\n| 27 May 2019\n|-\n|\n|13\n|3\n|16 March 2020\n|present\n|}\n\n==Reception==\nA lot of \"conservatives\" like [[:el:\u039a\u03ce\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03ad\u03ba\u03b1\u03c2|Kostas Prekas]] have criticised the show for \"crossing the line\", stating that \"...they are making fun of everybody, they are pricks. This show must end.\". The hosts have largely not paid attention to such statements, opting instead to make fun of them through their videos. \n\nThe show still remains one of the most popular shows on Greek television, especially among younger audiences. \n==Etymology==\n\"Radio Arvyla\" is a Greek idiom that means \"false rumor\" or fake \"news\". Literally it means \"Army-boot Radio\".\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:ANT1 shows]]\n[[Category:2008 Greek television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2000s Greek television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Greek television series]]\n[[Category:Greek comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Satirical publications]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Radio Arvyla\n| image                    = Radio arvyla.jpg\n| genre                    = Satirical Talk-Show\n| creator                  = Antonis Kanakis\n| director                 = Antonis Kanakis\n| presenter                = Antonis Kanakis<br> Giannis Servetas<br> Stathis Panagiotopoulos<br> Christos Kiousis<br>\n| composer                 = \n| opentheme                = \"[[Sugar Baby Love]]\"<br>by [[The Rubettes]] <ref>http://www.musicheaven.gr/html/modules.php?name=Splatt_Forums&file=viewtopic&topic=15248</ref>\n| country                  = [[Greece]]\n| language                 = [[Greek language|Greek]]\n| num_seasons              = 11\n| runtime                  = 90 minutes\n| network                  = [[ANT1]] (2008-2018)<br> [[Skai TV]] (2019)<br>[[YouTube]](2020-)\n| picture_format           = [[576i]] [[SDTV]]<br>[[1080i]] [[HDTV]]\n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = 14 April 2008\n| preceded_by              = [[A.M.A.N. (TV series)|A.M.A.N.]]\n| related                  = \n| website                  = http://www.antenna.gr/radioarvyla\n}}\n'''''Radio Arvyla''''' ({{lang-el|\u03a1\u03ac\u03b4\u03b9\u03bf \u0391\u03c1\u03b2\u03cd\u03bb\u03b1}}) is a Greek live panel show, filmed in [[Thessaloniki]] and airing on [[ANT1]].<ref>http://www.antenna.gr/minisites/radio-arvila/home</ref> It first aired on April 2008. It is hosted by [[Antonis Kanakis]], Giannis Servetas, Stathis Panagiotopoulos and Christos Kiousis. It mainly criticizes the political life and what prevails in the modern social life through parodies,videos, comedy Sketches and jokes.\nAs of 2016-17 season, it airs every other Monday, from 23.15 to 00.30, although it used to air from 18.00 to 19.00 during the 2007-2008 and 2008-2009 seasons. The first episode of season 4 aired on 11 October 2010.<ref>http://www.e-daily.gr/viral/74070/radio-arvyla-kathe-pote-tha-provalletai-h-ekpomph-video</ref><ref>http://www.gossip-tv.gr/media-tv/story/468944/h-epistrofi-ton-radio-arvyla-kai-i-anakoinosi-toy-antoni-kanaki</ref> All episodes from Season 3 and on are available online on the official website of [[ANT1]].<ref>http://www.antenna.gr/minisites/radio-arvila/episodes</ref><ref>http://www.newsit.gr/melas-blogposts/telos-oi-radio-arvyla/2207539/</ref><ref>http://www.iefimerida.gr/news/360613/anatropi-