 currently undergoing [[clinical trials]].  It is currently being licensed by Helicon Therapeutics in San Diego, California.  It was originally discovered and tested as part of a preclinical anti-inflammatory program by Inflazyme Pharmaceuticals.<ref name=\"pmid17823313\">{{cite journal  |vauthors=MacDonald E, Van der Lee H, Pocock D, etal |title=A novel phosphodiesterase type 4 inhibitor, HT-0712, enhances rehabilitation-dependent motor recovery and cortical reorganization after focal cortical ischemia |journal=Neurorehabil Neural Repair |volume=21 |issue=6 |pages=486\u201396 |year=2007 |pmid=17823313 |doi=10.1177/1545968307305521 |url=}}</ref>\n\n==Mechanism of action==\nHT-0712 appears to act as a [[PDE4 inhibitor]], thereby increasing [[Cyclic adenosine monophosphate|cAMP]] levels.  When cAMP levels are increased in neurons, this may trigger activation of cAMP response element-binding proteins ([[CREB]]).  CREBs are [[transcription factor]]s involved in the formation of [[long-term memory]].<ref name=\"pmid17823313\"/>\n\nThe side effects of the drug are not yet fully known.\n\n==Research==\nA 2014 study found that HT-0712 significantly boosted memory formation in mice. Data also indicated that HT-0712 may be effective to treat age-associated memory impairment in humans. <ref>{{cite journal|title=The PDE4 inhibitor HT-0712 improves hippocampus-dependent memory in aged mice| pmid=24964813 | doi=10.1038/npp.2014.154 | volume=39| issue=13| pmc=4229572| journal=Neuropsychopharmacology| pages=2938\u201348 | last1 = Peters | first1 = M | last2 = Bletsch | first2 = M | last3 = Stanley | first3 = J | last4 = Wheeler | first4 = D | last5 = Scott | first5 = R | last6 = Tully | first6 = T| year=2014 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.freepatentsonline.com/20040224316.html United States Patent 20040224316]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060303170837/http://www.helicontherapeutics.com/PDFs_%26_supporting_files/HT-0712_Phase_1_press_release_December_10_2004.pdf PDF file regarding Helicon's commencement of Phase I trials]\n\n{{Phosphodiesterase inhibitors}}\n\n[[Category:Lactams]]\n[[Category:Nootropics]]\n[[Category:PDE4 inhibitors]]\n[[Category:Phenol ethers]]\n[[Category:Piperidines]]\n", "text_old": "{{Drugbox\n| verifiedrevid = 411533590\n| IUPAC_name = (3''S'',5''S'')-5-(3-(Cyclopentyloxy)-4-methoxyphenyl)-3-(3-methylbenzyl)piperidin-2-one\n| image = HT-0712.svg\n| width = 250\n\n<!--Clinical data-->\n| tradename =\n| pregnancy_AU = <!-- A / B1 / B2 / B3 / C / D / X -->\n| pregnancy_US = <!-- A / B / C / D / X -->\n| pregnancy_category =\n| legal_AU = <!-- Unscheduled / S2 / S3 / S4 / S5 / S6 / S7 / S8 / S9 -->\n| legal_CA = <!-- Schedule I -->\n| legal_UK = <!-- Class A -->\n| legal_US = <!-- Schedule I -->\n| legal_status =\n| routes_of_administration =\n\n<!--Pharmacokinetic data-->\n| bioavailability =\n| protein_bound =\n| metabolism =\n| elimination_half-life =\n| excretion =\n\n<!--Identifiers-->\n| CAS_number = 617720-02-2\n| ATC_prefix = None\n| ATC_suffix =\n| PubChem = 9865375\n| DrugBank =\n| ChemSpiderID_Ref = {{chemspidercite|correct|chemspider}}\n| ChemSpiderID = 8041067\n\n<!--Chemical data-->\n| C=25 | H=31 | N=1 | O=3 \n| molecular_weight = 393.53 g/mol\n| smiles = O=C3NC[C@H](c2cc(OC1CCCC1)c(OC)cc2)C[C@H]3Cc4cccc(c4)C\n| StdInChI_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChI = 1S/C25H31NO3/c1-17-6-5-7-18(12-17)13-20-14-21(16-26-25(20)27)19-10-11-23(28-2)24(15-19)29-22-8-3-4-9-22/h5-7,10-12,15,20-22H,3-4,8-9,13-14,16H2,1-2H3,(H,26,27)/t20-,21-/m1/s1\n| StdInChIKey_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChIKey = ABEJDMOBAFLQNJ-NHCUHLMSSA-N\n| synonyms = HT-0712, IPL 455,903\n}}\n\n'''HT-0712''', also known as IPL-455903,<ref name=\"pmid18660832\">{{cite journal |author=Giembycz MA |title=Can the anti-inflammatory potential of PDE4 inhibitors be realized: guarded optimism or wishful thinking? |journal=Br. J. Pharmacol. |volume=155 |issue=3 |pages=288\u201390 |date=October 2008 |pmid=18660832 |pmc=2567889 |doi=10.1038/bjp.2008.297 |url=}}</ref> is an experimental [[cognitive]] enhancing [[medication|drug]] ([[nootropic]]) which is currently undergoing [[clinical trials]].  It is currently being licensed by Helicon Therapeutics in San Diego, California.  It was originally discovered and tested as part of a preclinical anti-inflammatory program by Inflazyme Pharmaceuticals.<ref name=\"pmid17823313\">{{cite journal  |vauthors=MacDonald E, Van der Lee H, Pocock D, etal |title=A novel phosphodiesterase type 4 inhibitor, HT-0712, enhances rehabilitation-dependent motor recovery and cortical reorganization after focal cortical ischemia |journal=Neurorehabil Neural Repair |volume=21 |issue=6 |pages=486\u201396 |year=2007 |pmid=17823313 |doi=10.1177/1545968307305521 |url=}}</ref>\n\n==Mechanism of action==\nHT-0712 appears to act as a [[PDE4 inhibitor]], thereby increasing [[Cyclic adenosine monophosphate|cAMP]] levels.  When cAMP levels are increased in neurons, this may trigger activation of cAMP response element-binding proteins ([[CREB]]).  CREBs are [[transcription factor]]s involved in the formation of [[long-term memory]].<ref name=\"pmid17823313\"/>\n\nThe side effects of the drug are not yet fully known.\n\n==Research==\nA 2014 study found that HT-0712 significantly boosted memory formation in mice. Data also indicated that HT-0712 may be effective to treat age-associated memory impairment in humans. <ref>{{cite journal|title=The PDE4 inhibitor HT-0712 improves hippocampus-dependent memory in aged mice| pmid=24964813 | doi=10.1038/npp.2014.154 | volume=39| issue=13| pmc=4229572| journal=Neuropsychopharmacology| pages=2938\u201348 | last1 = Peters | first1 = M | last2 = Bletsch | first2 = M | last3 = Stanley | first3 = J | last4 = Wheeler | first4 = D | last5 = Scott | first5 = R | last6 = Tully | first6 = T| year=2014 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.freepatentsonline.com/20040224316.html United States Patent 20040224316]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060303170837/http://www.helicontherapeutics.com/PDFs_%26_supporting_files/HT-0712_Phase_1_press_release_December_10_2004.pdf PDF file regarding Helicon's commencement of Phase I trials]\n\n{{Phosphodiesterase inhibitors}}\n\n[[Category:Lactams]]\n[[Category:Nootropics]]\n[[Category:PDE4 inhibitors]]\n[[Category:Phenol ethers]]\n[[Category:Piperidines]]\n", "name_user": "Fswitzer4", "label": "safe", "comment": "added FDA UNII to drug box", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HT-0712"}
